subSubSection.paragraph:
Female. Subgenital plate wide at base with converging lateral margins and elevated disc; disc in basal half provided with a narrow medial carina in midline; surface of disc in dried specimens slightly concave; apical margin of disc truncate, straight, and provided at both lateral angles with a rather long, obliquely up-bent spine-like process with subacute tip (
Figs 5H–L
). Ovipositor about one and a half time as long as body; behind basal constriction straight with dorsal valves in basal half faintly convex (
Fig. 1D
).
